# Privacy Policy for 6-6-6 High-Lo

**Effective date:** February 13, 2026  
**Last updated:** February 13, 2026

6-6-6 High-Lo (“the App”) is provided by Frank Gasparovic (“we,” “us,” or “our”).

This Privacy Policy explains what information the App collects, how it is used, and your choices.

## 1. Information We Collect

### Information you provide in the App
- Player names
- Pops/handicap settings
- Hole scores and round settings
- Course search text and selected course details
- Round history data

### Information collected automatically
The App uses third-party SDKs and services that may collect technical information such as:
- Device identifiers (for ads)
- IP address
- App/device diagnostics and performance data
- Approximate location derived from IP (via third-party services)

## 2. How We Use Information

We use information to:
- Run core app features (scoring, match calculations, round history)
- Show advertising
- Improve app stability and performance
- Enable course search functionality

## 3. Third-Party Services

The App uses third-party providers, including:

- **Google Mobile Ads (AdMob)** for ads  
  Google Privacy Policy: https://policies.google.com/privacy

- **GolfCourseAPI** for golf course lookup  
  Service site: https://api.golfcourseapi.com

- **Venmo deep links** (optional) to open Venmo for payment/request actions  
  We do not process payments directly in the App.

These providers may process data according to their own privacy policies.

## 4. Data Storage and Retention

- Round and scoring data are stored locally on your device.
- If iCloud device backup is enabled, your device backup may include app data.
- We do not maintain user accounts or host your round history on our own servers.

## 5. Your Choices

- You can stop all collection by uninstalling the App.
- You can manage ad/privacy permissions in iOS settings (including tracking permissions where applicable).
- You can contact us to request deletion guidance for locally stored app data.

## 6. Children’s Privacy

The App is not directed to children under 13, and we do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13.

## 7. Security

We use reasonable measures to protect information handled by the App, but no method of transmission or storage is completely secure.

## 8. International Users

Third-party providers may process data on servers located outside your country.

## 9. Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Updates will be posted at this same URL with a revised “Last updated” date.

## 10. Contact

If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, contact:

**Frank Gasparovic**  
**Email:** Frank.Gasparovic@Gmail.com
